Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving navigation strategies for mobile robots in unstructured environments. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning approach to improve navigation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper presents an extension of the residual reinforcement learning framework. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of visual input for navigation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but relevant as the paper discusses the use of a classical controller in combination with a learned residual control effect.
